description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dynamic Assistant Technical Officer to become a part of our Pharmacy team based within the Princess Alexandra Hospital in Harlow, Essex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The new Medical and Surgical Assessment Centre will be a two-storey extension adjacent to the emergency department (ED) at the front of the hospital and next to Charnley Ward. This will improve the facilities available for our patients ahead of the completion of the new hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you will be responsible for assisting the Pharmacy Technicians to provide an accurate and efficient service in the pharmacy stores, dispensary and on wards, as well as the purchasing office or aseptic department. No two days will be the same and you will receive training in each area as you rotate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return we can offer support and development to complete your Pharmacy Services Assistant Qualification if needed, a varied job based qualification which will see you rotate through all pharmacy departments to learn new skills as well as opportunities for further specialised training and progression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For this role you will need to have good GCSE’s in Maths, English Language and Science and the ability to complete the Pharmacy Services Assistant Qualification. Pharmaceutical experience is not essential but you must have an interest in and demonstrate enthusiasm for this field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHannah LeMarJob titleEducation, Training and Personnel ManagerEmail addressh.lemar@nhs.netTelephone number01279827056Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Available for informal calls or visits Monday-Wednesday 08.30-16.30&lt;/p&gt;
